Paper: hep-th/0012093

Date: 2000-12-11

Title: Traveling Faster than the Speed of Light in Non-Commutative Geometry

Authors: Akikazu Hashimoto and N. Itzhaki

Comments: 16 pages 3 figures, references added

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D63 (2001) 126004

We study various dynamical aspects of solitons in non-commutative gaugetheories and find surprising results. Among them is the observation that thesolitons can travel faster than the speed of light for arbitrarily longdistances.